We need to prove the TUTTE-BERGE formula for the size of a maximum matching in an arbitrary graph. The theorem states that:

For any graph $G$ and subset $X \subseteq V(G)$, 
$$ \nu(G) \leq \frac{1}{2}(|V(G)| + |X| - \text{odd}(G - X)) $$
where $\nu(G)$ is the size of a maximum matching of $G$, and $\text{odd}(G - X)$ is the number of components of $G - X$ that have an odd number of vertices.

Furthermore, if $X$ is a maximal subset such that $\nu(G - X) = \nu(G) - |X|$, then 
$$ \nu(G - X) = \frac{1}{2}(|V(G - X)| - \text{odd}(G - X)) $$
which implies 
$$ \nu(G) = \frac{1}{2}(|V(G)| + |X| - \text{odd}(G - X)) $$

